Lack of appetite, isolating yourself.

513
00:33:50,195 --> 00:33:53,322
Uncontrollable urination and blacking
out are good predictors of what?

514
00:33:53,448 --> 00:33:54,281
Seizure.

515
00:33:54,408 --> 00:33:56,867
Which means the seizure he had
when you tested his heart

516
00:33:56,993 --> 00:33:58,911
- was at least his second seizure.
- So what?

517
00:33:59,037 --> 00:34:00,677
Depression and seizures
aren't correlated.

518
00:34:00,706 --> 00:34:03,332
No, but you know what is?

519
00:34:03,458 --> 00:34:06,168
Depression
and anti-depression medicine.

520
00:34:06,294 --> 00:34:07,712
Tox screen was clean.

521
00:34:07,838 --> 00:34:10,047
Yeah, but you know how much
crap he's got in his system

522
00:34:10,173 --> 00:34:11,340
for dealing with those burns.

523
00:34:11,466 --> 00:34:14,227
The guy could have the Spanish Armada
floating through his bloodstream

524
00:34:14,261 --> 00:34:16,971
and we wouldn't know about it,
till they started firing cannons.

525
00:34:17,097 --> 00:34:20,558
Antidepressants have been known to cause
seizures in kids, but not orgasms.

526
00:34:20,684 --> 00:34:21,765
This is a brain in trouble.

527
00:34:21,810 --> 00:34:24,854
This is a brain
with too much serotonin.

528
00:34:24,980 --> 00:34:28,691
Serotonin affects mood, appetite, it
doesn't cause the brain to shut down.

529
00:34:28,817 --> 00:34:31,944
Antidepressants fake brains into
thinking they have more serotonin

530
00:34:32,070 --> 00:34:33,195
than they actually do.

531
00:34:33,321 --> 00:34:37,199
Every ten million or so cases
sets off a chain reaction.

532
00:34:37,325 --> 00:34:39,827
Produces too much,
enough to fry itself.

533
00:34:39,953 --> 00:34:42,371
If Adam has Serotonin Storm,
it's deadly.

534
00:34:42,497 --> 00:34:44,498
But treatable. Cyproheptadine.

535
00:34:44,624 --> 00:34:46,292
Unless he doesn't have
Serotonin Storm.

536
00:34:46,418 --> 00:34:48,919
He could just as easily have too
much dopamine as serotonin,

537
00:34:49,045 --> 00:34:52,465
but if it's dopamine, the
cyproheptadine will kill him.

538
00:34:52,591 --> 00:34:53,424
Where are you going?

539
00:34:53,550 --> 00:34:55,509
Gonna talk to the kid again,
he seems nice.

540
00:34:55,635 --> 00:34:57,052
You can't.

541
00:34:57,304 --> 00:34:58,929
Why? Did he say
he doesn't like me?

542
00:34:59,055 --> 00:35:02,183
Anesthesiologist
told the parents what you did.

543
00:35:02,309 --> 00:35:04,351
Everyone's a tattletale.

544
00:35:10,650 --> 00:35:12,485
Is your son depressed?

545
00:35:14,196 --> 00:35:16,530
- No. Who are you?
- I'm Dr. House.

546
00:35:16,656 --> 00:35:18,017
Oh, you're the idiot
who thought...

547
00:35:18,074 --> 00:35:19,784
I heard him screaming
all the way down the hallway.

548
00:35:19,910 --> 00:35:22,710
If I didn't wake him up, I wouldn't
have learned what caused the crash.

549
00:35:22,829 --> 00:35:24,330
He had a seizure.

550
00:35:27,793 --> 00:35:29,585
This wasn't my fault?

551
00:35:30,504 --> 00:35:33,714
Well, if he hadn't had the brain
problem, he wouldn't have the burns.

552
00:35:33,840 --> 00:35:35,925
On the other hand, if you
hadn't put him on the ATV,

553
00:35:36,051 --> 00:35:37,301
he also
wouldn't have the burns.

554
00:35:37,427 --> 00:35:39,345
You can debate your personal
responsibility after I leave.

555
00:35:39,471 --> 00:35:41,055
I need to wake him up again.

556
00:35:41,181 --> 00:35:42,982
I need to know if
he's taking antidepressants.

557
00:35:43,058 --> 00:35:44,099
He's not.

558
00:35:45,143 --> 00:35:48,813
- He's the happiest kid I know.
- But you don't know, do you?

559
00:35:51,024 --> 00:35:52,274
He's my son.

560
00:35:52,984 --> 00:35:54,568
That's sort of my point.

561
00:35:54,694 --> 00:35:58,155
At 16, they'll tell anyone
anything, except their parents.

562
00:35:58,281 --> 00:35:59,865
Adam talks to us
about everything.

563
00:35:59,991 --> 00:36:02,034
Yeah, I know
about the pot and the cocaine.

564
00:36:02,160 --> 00:36:04,036
There was never... Cocaine.
What...

565
00:36:04,162 --> 00:36:07,248
Are you sure?
Are you having him followed?

566
00:36:07,374 --> 00:36:09,834
He told us
when he got drunk at a party.

567
00:36:09,960 --> 00:36:11,710
He told us
when he started having sex.

568
00:36:11,837 --> 00:36:13,420
At 16? Way to go.

569
00:36:13,547 --> 00:36:15,187
He told us when he
cheated on a math test.

570
00:36:15,298 --> 00:36:17,550
He told us when his
girlfriend cheated on him.

571
00:36:17,676 --> 00:36:20,594
- He doesn't hide anything from us.
- But if he was depressed?

572
00:36:20,720 --> 00:36:21,762
He'd tell us.

573
00:36:22,222 --> 00:36:25,015
We don't judge, he's not
depressed, we're sure.

574
00:36:25,141 --> 00:36:27,268
"Bet his life on it" sure?

575
00:36:29,104 --> 00:36:30,855
Just hypothetically.

576
00:36:32,315 --> 00:36:33,440
Yeah.

577
00:36:37,112 --> 00:36:37,987
Okay.

578
00:36:41,032 --> 00:36:42,324
Kid's happy.

579
00:36:43,243 --> 00:36:45,286
Happy, happy, happy.

580
00:36:45,662 --> 00:36:49,164
Then we're back to where we started.
Seizure disorders.

581
00:36:49,291 --> 00:36:52,126
Seizure disorders
aren't causing orgasms.

582
00:36:52,252 --> 00:36:53,752
Vascular malformations?

583
00:36:53,879 --> 00:36:55,921
Would've seen it
on the sonogram.

584
00:36:56,047 --> 00:36:58,090
Hepatic encephalopathy?

585
00:36:58,216 --> 00:37:00,301
Liver enzyme tests were normal.

586
00:37:06,266 --> 00:37:08,851
- Where are you going?
- Take a leak.

587
00:37:16,943 --> 00:37:18,110
What are you doing?

588
00:37:18,236 --> 00:37:20,195
You can't come in here,
you're not sterile.

589
00:37:20,322 --> 00:37:21,530
Don't touch our son,
we told you...

590
00:37:21,656 --> 00:37:24,116
Seriously, millions of
bacteria, microbes on you.

591
00:37:24,242 --> 00:37:27,119
He'll die of sepsis.
If you go in there...

592
00:37:31,166 --> 00:37:32,625
I think
he's gonna wake him up again.

593
00:37:32,751 --> 00:37:34,168
I know he is.

594
00:37:36,129 --> 00:37:37,880
House, you can't do this.

595
00:37:38,006 --> 00:37:42,134
Oh, if I had a nickel for every
time I've heard that. Relax.

596
00:37:42,260 --> 00:37:45,763
Are they gonna sue us?
If I'm right, I save his life.

597
00:37:45,889 --> 00:37:48,807
If I'm wrong,
he's dead no matter what I do.

598
00:37:49,225 --> 00:37:52,186
Either way, how much
have I really hurt them?

599
00:37:52,312 --> 00:37:53,354
Leave him alone!

600
00:37:53,480 --> 00:37:55,940
You're not sterile.
Do you wanna kill the kid?

601
00:37:56,066 --> 00:37:57,983
- Give me the syringe.
- No pain, no gain.

602
00:37:58,109 --> 00:38:00,069
Hey, you gotta stop this.

603
00:38:04,115 --> 00:38:05,699
They're right.

604
00:38:06,534 --> 00:38:09,203
- He's not depressed.
- Yeah, sure.

605
00:38:09,329 --> 00:38:12,081
I'm not letting you go
till you give me that syringe.

606
00:38:12,207 --> 00:38:14,166
What's that on his wrist?

607
00:38:15,251 --> 00:38:16,293
A burn.

608
00:38:16,419 --> 00:38:18,796
- Why on his wrist?
- Why not on his wrist?

609
00:38:18,922 --> 00:38:22,758
His back, his torso, everything's a mess.
His forearms are clean.

610
00:38:22,884 --> 00:38:25,094
- Except right there.
- So what?

611
00:38:26,388 --> 00:38:27,846
It's a perfect circle.

612
00:38:27,973 --> 00:38:32,059
So a drop of burning gasoline fell
on his wrist, a screw from the ATV.

613
00:38:32,978 --> 00:38:34,186
Maybe.

614
00:38:44,280 --> 00:38:47,157
- Why are you torturing him?
- Does your son smoke?

615
00:38:48,284 --> 00:38:49,868
I'd kill him.

616
00:38:51,871 --> 00:38:56,083
So, he can talk to you about sex,
crack, anything except cigarettes.

617
00:38:57,377 --> 00:39:00,129
He has a cigarette burn
on his wrist.

618
00:39:00,630 --> 00:39:03,966
Also a fading nicotine stain
between two fingers.

619
00:39:04,718 --> 00:39:07,970
Bad news, your son has a
filthy, unhealthy habit.

620
00:39:08,096 --> 00:39:10,264
Good news, he's trying to quit.

621
00:39:10,390 --> 00:39:12,516
Bad news,
the quitting's killing him.

622
00:39:12,642 --> 00:39:15,352
Good news,
I can cure him. Bad news...

623
00:39:16,938 --> 00:39:21,316
- Nope, that's the end of it.
- Quitting smoking can kill?

624
00:39:21,443 --> 00:39:23,444
No-smoke meds
are antidepressants.

625
00:39:23,570 --> 00:39:25,612
The crappy ones
you get over the Internet

626
00:39:25,739 --> 00:39:28,449
are loaded with whatever
antidepressants they can get cheap.

627
00:39:28,575 --> 00:39:32,911
And since Mommy and Daddy obviously
didn't take him to a pediatrician...

628
00:39:35,123 --> 00:39:38,333
Sorry, I was wrong
about him being depressed.

629
00:39:38,835 --> 00:39:40,252
Treat him.

630
00:39:58,313 --> 00:39:59,354
Hey!

631
00:40:00,482 --> 00:40:02,691
Did you drop acid?

632
00:40:04,319 --> 00:40:07,154
- Why would I do that?
- To annoy me.

633
00:40:07,322 --> 00:40:09,782
Or maybe because
you're miserable,

634
00:40:09,908 --> 00:40:13,243
or because
you want to self-destruct.

635
00:40:13,411 --> 00:40:14,787
Pick one.

636
00:40:15,371 --> 00:40:19,333
How about because LSD acts on
serotonin receptors in the brain,

637
00:40:19,459 --> 00:40:22,169
which can stop
a migraine in its tracks.

638
00:40:22,587 --> 00:40:25,172
I'm just saying
that's also a possibility.

639
00:40:25,298 --> 00:40:28,550
- How did you know about it?
- Cameron is worried about you.

640
00:40:28,676 --> 00:40:32,513
I told her that LSD lasts up to 12 hours,
if you were functional, she must be wrong.

641
00:40:32,639 --> 00:40:35,390
Either that or I also took a
whole bunch of antidepressants,

642
00:40:35,517 --> 00:40:37,601
which short-circuited the LSD.

643
00:40:37,727 --> 00:40:39,478
I'm just saying
that would also explain it.

644
00:40:39,604 --> 00:40:41,939
Thank you for ruining
my clinical trials.

645
00:40:42,065 --> 00:40:44,024
Pharmaceutical company's
shutting me down.

646
00:40:44,150 --> 00:40:46,401
- You're kidding. Really?
- How could that surprise you?

647
00:40:46,528 --> 00:40:47,486
You sent them an email

648
00:40:47,612 --> 00:40:50,280
complaining about my math,
telling them about your stunt.

649
00:40:50,406 --> 00:40:52,366
I didn't know
people actually read emails.

650
00:40:52,492 --> 00:40:54,053
Delete button's
so conveniently located.

651
00:40:54,160 --> 00:40:56,912
So what's next?
You gonna follow me my whole life?

652
00:40:57,038 --> 00:40:58,747
- Torture me?
- Why would I do that?

653
00:40:58,873 --> 00:41:00,905
You waited 20 years to do this.
What's next?

654
00:41:00,918 --> 00:41:02,960
Break up my marriage?

655
00:41:03,837 --> 00:41:07,172
- No. We're even.
- Right.

656
00:41:09,300 --> 00:41:11,301
Oh, thanks for setting me up.

657
00:41:15,181 --> 00:41:18,392
Eye for an eye,
LSD and antidepressants.

658
00:41:19,394 --> 00:41:21,186
Everything in balance.

659
00:41:21,312 --> 00:41:24,356
Buddhists call it Karma. Christians
call it the Golden Rule.

660
00:41:24,482 --> 00:41:25,941
Jews call it...

661
00:41:27,986 --> 00:41:31,321
I don't know, Rabbi Hillel
said something poignant.

662
00:41:32,532 --> 00:41:35,075
Universe
always settles the score.

663
00:41:35,743 --> 00:41:38,328
- Does it?
- No.

664
00:41:40,206 --> 00:41:41,623
But it should.

665
00:41:49,257 --> 00:41:53,260
Do you think you'll ever be able
to look at him and not blame me?

666
00:41:54,137 --> 00:41:57,181
Yeah. Will you?

667
00:42:49,234 --> 00:42:50,400
I'm Paula.

668
00:42:50,735 --> 00:42:53,237
- Hey, Paula.
- How you doing?

669
00:42:54,906 --> 00:42:57,950
You work over at the college, or
are you full-time over at the...

670
00:42:58,076 --> 00:43:00,369
I'm looking for a distraction.

671
00:43:01,079 --> 00:43:03,956
You don't need to talk
to do that, do you?

